This paper discusses the use of wireless technologies for smart grid applications, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the challenges of wireless communication in the smart grid, which relates to information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the need for high reliability in communication, which is a concern in computer security (cs.CR) and cyber-physical systems (cs.CY).
